nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

playstore_details.title: Bitso - Buy and sell bitcoin
playstore_details.description:
At Bitso, we’re evolving the way people use their money. We make cryptocurrencies as easy as ordering pizza.

In our app, you can buy and sell bitcoin or any other cryptocurrencies available, store them all in one place or send them to friends and family.

Simple
✔ ️Fund Argentine pesos or Mexican pesos instantly from your mobile bank account 
✔ Buy and sell bitcoin, ether, XRP, and other cryptocurrencies in a few taps 
✔ Use Bitso Transfer to send and receive cryptocurrencies or pesos

Transparent
✔ Check the price of bitcoin and any other cryptocurrency in real-time, and choose the best time to buy and sell 
✔ Take control of every movement by using a security code and face ID
✔ Store your cryptocurrencies in one place 

Global
✔ Join a community of more than 1 million users 
✔ Operate with Mexican pesos or Argentine pesos
✔ Buy and sell bitcoin, ether, or XRP, and get US dollars

About Bitso
Bitso is a financial services platform powered by blockchain technology. With more than 1 million users, operates in Mexico and Argentina. Buy and sell bitcoin, ether, XRP, litecoin, bitcoin cash, trueUSD, mana, BAT, and DAI.

It's time to change the way you see and use your money.
